## Beginner-Safe Starter Signal

OpenClaw 4.29 may make agents feel easier to operate because steering, replies, memory, and follow-ups are becoming more usable.

That does not mean beginners should start with broad automation.

Stackfax beginner-safe verdict:

Starter-Ready / Guardrails Required

Good starter permissions:

- observe
- summarize
- draft
- report
- ask for approval

Avoid at first:

- sending messages automatically
- touching customer data
- moving or deleting files
- accessing wallets
- editing records
- connecting sensitive credentials
- running unattended workflows
- modifying production systems
- creating external follow-ups without review

