## Agent ROI Signal

Steering, memory, visible replies, and follow-ups can make agents more useful.

But more capability does not automatically mean more value.

Stackfax signal:

Agent ROI should measure useful completed work, not agent activity.

Possible Stackfax categories:

- Agent ROI Review
- Activity vs Outcome
- Supervision Cost
- Cleanup Cost
- Compounding Value
- Workflow Fit Review

Useful line:

A more capable agent still has to earn its seat.

Agent ROI questions:

- Did the agent finish useful work?
- Did steering reduce failure or increase babysitting?
- Did memory improve output or create cleanup?
- Did follow-ups help or annoy?
- Did visible replies improve trust?
- Did subagents improve quality or add complexity?

