## Field Research Verdict

OpenClaw 4.29 supports the Stackfax thesis.

As agent platforms become easier to steer, remember, message, route, and follow up, users need stronger guardrails.

They need help deciding:

- who can steer the agent
- what the agent can remember
- where the agent can reply
- what follow-ups it can create
- which subagent handled what
- which provider handled what
- what changed after the update
- what requires human approval
- what needs a run receipt
- when to recheck

Final field note:

Capability without governance becomes hidden risk.

Steer the agent.

Receipt the run.

Approve the action.
